i’m sorry to my followers who don’t give a damn about mystic messenger character analysis

while he holds his own worldview still (the one of unknown) his mood is much calmer. because he doesn’t just have one trait. he’s an alter and his own person with various emotions and as much depth as ray has, and as post-good-end saeran has when they’ve integrated.

he can hyperfixate for weeks on crafting a little bizarre puppet show and performing it for MC. in seven’s route, we see lapses where he can be calm and living a domestic life. hell, in his own route we see him confront the MC while coming down from a paranoid state.

he can talk to MC nicely in other routes, he can enjoy spying on the chatroom and find them amusing, he can enjoy their favorite ice cream, he can look at the stars and wish for freedom himself (a trait that is usually tied to ray),

and these are the extremes of their thought processes. they are not always feeling this paranoia + delusion at 100% intensity, they can be calmed down and experience joys. as such, unknown can even be kind and enjoy things simply because he’s not JUST a manifestation of rage.

ray => “to combat being weak, i must be subservient to others, others will hold control over me, i need to choose who i serve with purpose, i need to be helpful to those i serve in any way, no matter what”

the establishing principle to both their world views is that they are weak. 

unknown => “to combat being weak, i must act strong, i must be in control of others, i must show i am strong in any possible way i can, no matter what.”

ray feels rage as well! he just shows it differently and doesn’t get a chance to be angry while conscious because rage is an emotion that triggers unknown to front. but rather it's  their views and how they react to their emotions.

even when unknown/“suit saeran” is the alter fronting he is not just enraged all the time even if that’s a lot of what we see directed towards the MC in his route. the real distinguisher between him and ray isn’t rage,

positive: confirmation of negative worldview/praised on being “useful” “strong” , enabling of destructive behaviors, affection (leads to abandonment paranoia), his interests/favorites, being overworked, childhood memories, etc.

negative: perceived abandonment, feelings of inferiority/faced with someone perceived as “better than him”, being told he’s weak, SEEING his own “weakness” or seeing it reflected in others, perceived betrayal, etc.
he doesn’t just call any and everything “stupid” “pathetic” etc. his anger is usually in response to specific negative and positive stimuli.

saeran, even as unknown or “suit saeran”, isn’t just angry and bitchy and pessimistic all the time without reason.. even if the reasoning is illogical it’s set up as a specific defense mechanism due to both his bpd and osdd that makes sense in his mind
